<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Disaster Safety Guide</h1>
        <p>Learn how to stay safe during floods, cyclones, and earthquakes</p>
        <div class="wave"></div>
    </header>
    
    <div class="container">
        <section class="intro">
            <h2>Be Prepared, Stay Safe</h2>
            <p>Natural disasters can strike with little warning, but knowing what to do before, during, and after can save lives. This interactive guide provides essential information on how to prepare for and respond to three common types of disasters: floods, cyclones, and earthquakes.</p>
            <p>Select a disaster type below to learn specific safety measures:</p>
        </section>
        
        <div class="disaster-tabs">
            <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="flood">
                <span>Flood Safety</span>
            </button>
            <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="cyclone">
                <span>Cyclone Safety</span>
            </button>
            <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="earthquake">
                <span>Earthquake Safety</span>
            </button>
        </div>
        
        <div id="flood" class="tab-content active">
            <div class="checklist">
                <h2>Flood Safety Measures</h2>
                <p>Floods can develop slowly or happen suddenly without warning. Being prepared can help keep you and your family safe.</p>
                
                <div class="dos-donts">
                    <div class="dos">
                        <h3>Do's</h3>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Create an emergency plan and prepare an emergency kit with essential supplies</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Monitor weather forecasts and flood warnings regularly</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Move valuable items, electrical equipment, and chemicals to higher levels</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Turn off gas, water, and electricity if instructed to evacuate</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Evacuate immediately if advised by authorities</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Avoid walking or driving through flood waters - just 6 inches of water can knock you down</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Drink only bottled or boiled water until authorities declare the water supply safe</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="donts">
                        <h3>Don'ts</h3>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't ignore evacuation orders from officials</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't drive around barricades - they are there for your safety</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't drive through flooded areas - just 12 inches of water can float a car</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't touch electrical equipment if you are wet or standing in water</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't use tap water until authorities declare it safe</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't return home until authorities say it is safe to do so</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't enter a building surrounded by floodwaters</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="cyclone" class="tab-content">
            <div class="checklist">
                <h2>Cyclone Safety Measures</h2>
                <p>Cyclones (also known as hurricanes or typhoons) bring strong winds, heavy rainfall, storm surges, and potential flooding. Preparation is key to survival.</p>
                
                <div class="dos-donts">
                    <div class="dos">
                        <h3>Do's</h3>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Create an emergency plan and prepare a cyclone kit well before cyclone season</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Know your evacuation route and plan where to go if you must leave</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Secure loose items around your property and trim trees before cyclone season</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Install storm shutters or board up windows with plywood when a cyclone is approaching</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Fill bathtubs and containers with water for washing and cleaning if water supply fails</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Stay indoors during a cyclone, away from windows and doors</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Listen to battery-powered radio for updates and instructions</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="donts">
                        <h3>Don'ts</h3>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't ignore evacuation orders - leave immediately if instructed</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't go outside during the "eye" of the cyclone - violent winds will return</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't use electrical equipment during the cyclone if there's lightning</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't use candles for lighting in case of gas leaks - use flashlights instead</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't go sightseeing after a cyclone - there may be dangers like downed power lines</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't drive through flooded roads - hidden dangers may exist below the water</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't delay preparations until the last minute - cyclones can intensify rapidly</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div id="earthquake" class="tab-content">
            <div class="checklist">
                <h2>Earthquake Safety Measures</h2>
                <p>Earthquakes strike without warning. Knowing how to react quickly and appropriately can prevent injuries and save lives.</p>
                
                <div class="dos-donts">
                    <div class="dos">
                        <h3>Do's</h3>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Drop, Cover, and Hold On - get under a sturdy table or desk and hold on</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Stay indoors until the shaking stops and you're sure it's safe to exit</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>If in bed during the earthquake, stay there and cover your head with a pillow</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>If outdoors, move to an open area away from buildings, trees, and power lines</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Keep an emergency kit ready with water, food, medicine, and essential supplies</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Know how to turn off gas, water, and electricity at main switches</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✓</i>
                            <div>Be prepared for aftershocks which can occur minutes, days, or weeks later</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="donts">
                        <h3>Don'ts</h3>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't run outside during shaking - most injuries occur when people try to move</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't stand in a doorway - modern doorways are no stronger than any other part of the house</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't use elevators during or after an earthquake</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't use matches, lighters, or any open flame inside until you're sure there are no gas leaks</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't touch fallen electrical wires or broken utility lines</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't re-enter damaged buildings until declared safe by authorities</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="checklist-item">
                            <i>✗</i>
                            <div>Don't spread rumors or unverified information about the disaster</div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <section class="interactive-section">
            <h2>Test Your Knowledge</h2>
            <p>Take this quick quiz to test your understanding of disaster safety measures.</p>
            
            <div class="quiz-container">
                <div class="quiz-question" id="question-1">
                    <h4>1. During a flood, how much water can float a car?</h4>
                    <div class="quiz-options">
                        <div class="quiz-option" data-correct="false">3 inches of water</div>
